attachments.text: As a law student, Bryan Stevenson was sent to a maximum security prison to meet a man on death row. The man told Stevenson he'd never met an African-American lawyer, and the two of them talked for

text: He’s a legend… he’s an amazing lawyer who has passed multiple pieces of new legislation through the supreme court about death row, he’s gotten over 100 wrongly accused people help who were on death row, and his book is freaking gold. A bit sad and truly depressing to see where our country was (and still, for a large part, is) but it is also uplifting and incredibly inspirational! I can bring the book in for whoever wants to borrow it! <http://www.eji.org/BryanStevenson>

attachments.title: Bryan Stevenson
attachments.text: BRYAN STEVENSON is the founder and Executive Director of the Equal Justice Initiative in Montgomery, Alabama. Mr. Stevenson is a widely acclaimed public interest lawyer who has dedicated his career to helping the poor, the incarcerated and the condemned.
